-- t17. The Demography of Sexuality: Queering Demographic Methods -- t18. What to Do with Actual People? Thinking Through a Queer Social Science Method -- t19. Queer Accounting: Methodological Investments and Disinvestments -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis provocative collection showcases the work of emerging and established sociologists in the fields of sexuality and gender studies as they reflect on what it means to develop, practice, and teach queer methods. Located within the critical conversation about the possibilities and challenges of utilizing insights from humanistic queer epistemologies in social scientific research, Other, Please Specify presents to a new generation of researchers an array of experiences, insights, and approaches, revealing the power of investigations of the social world. With contributions from sociologists who have helped define queer studies and who use a range of interpretative and statistical methods, this volume offers methodological advice and practical strategies in research design and execution, all with the intent of getting queer research off the ground and building a collaborative community within this emerging subfield.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aQueer theory. 0aSociologyxMethodology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aanti lgbt.  acollaborative communties in queer studies.  afeminism.  agender and feminism.  agender feminism lgbt.  agender studies.  ahumanistic queer epistemologies.  algbt.  algbtq social scientists.  algbtq studies.  algbtq.  apolitics and philosophy.  apractical strategies in queer methodologies.  aqueer books.  aqueer epistemologies.  aqueer methods.  aqueer research.  aqueer studies.